=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
The task: Identify the reaction center for the mapped transformation. Provide reaction_edit_summary presumably includes atoms changed? Need to output in format defined by expected_output_schema "reaction_edit_summary". Need to infer what that schema expects. Not given explicitly. But typical reaction_center identification answer: list of atoms with mapping numbers that change bonds? Reaction center includes atoms whose bond orders change. We have SMIRKS: "CCC(C#N)[C:20](=[N-:10])[O:21][P:22](Cl)(Cl)Cl.Cl>>CCC(C#N)[C:20]#[N:10].[O:21]=[P-:22](Cl)(Cl)Cl.Cl"

So reactant side: a carbon (C:20) attached to =N- (N:10) double bond, also attached to O:21 which attached to P:22 with three Cl. So it's a phosphoryl ester? Actually O-P(Cl)3.

Product side: carbon C:20 triple bonded to N:10 (C#N). O:21 double bonded to P- (P:22) with three Cl.

Thus reaction center includes atoms 20,10,21,22 with bond changes: C20=N10 double bond

